LAGOS  – The Lagos State office of the National Directorate of Employment has embarked on the registration of unemployed persons in the 20 local government areas in the state. The Lagos State Coordinator of the directorate, Mrs. Serena Olayebi Edward, in a statement issued at the Lagos office, said the registration started on 17thApril and will end 28th April 2023. She explained that the registration exercise will be held at NDE state office at 7 Barikisu Iyede Street, Onike Yaba, and the 20 local government areas in the state concurrently. The State Coordinator urged all unemployed in Lagos State to take advantage of the opportunity to register at their designated local governments in order to benefit from the programme. She stated that the Federal Government wants to create data of the unemployed in the country in order to make adequate plans for them.